evaluation.response:
It can feel so hard to feel like you lose control, even over something like your body. 

If it feels helpful to you right now, taking a walk after dinner is one way to try to help yourself feel more in control. However, there are many other helpful things you can do that also may help you feel more consistent also.&#x20;

If preciseness feels especially important to you, maybe try using a scale daily in the morning to help super monitor your body and feel in control of any changes. Also, anything from journaling, exercising, or stretching may also help and don't have to cost money.&#x20;

Everyone's body is very different, and your weight can be anywhere. Whoever you feel comfortable with can help you to work towards your goals. If it's someone from your support system that already knows you, you may want to start there.&#x20;
